<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>at home • on home ground</xh5><p> <i>at home</i>—(predic.) very competent in smth. <i>(with the implication that it makes a person feel confident and relaxed):</i> Melanie is equally <u>at home</u> singing oratorio, jazz or performing in musical theater.</p><p><i>on home ground—</i>1. in the area where one works or lives: It was nice to renew acquaintances of students I’ve taught and to meet them on “<u>home ground</u>.” 2. <i>= at home: </i>Godber is <u>on home ground</u>, writing with cold-eyed affection about the Yorkshire mining communities.</p> </entry>
